{
  "stem": "17135.5",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 284.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were not prepared.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, they-- they had no-- no room for us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Sometimes for three days we didn't get any food.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Then we got a potato, a stinking, rotten frozen potato.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was terrible.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And people got so emaciated.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I, myself, knew that if I go another week with this column, it will be the end.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I was-- I-- I think I was reduced to, at best-- at best, my weight was 70 pounds, at best.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I was skeleton like-- like you see in the pictures from Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Now, let me tell you what I did.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Because I was in-- in Buna, in Auschwitz III, I had connections-- you know, if you work for [? lageralteste. ?] At the end of Auschwitz, the last month, they didn't want to weave anymore the pajama suits.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "What they did is they took civilian clothes from the people that were arrested, and they took oil paint and made a big stripe that wide on the back of the jacket that was a sign that you are prisoner.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Everybody in Germany, every policeman, knew anyone who wears a jacket like this is a prisoner.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I said, I want a jacket like this, and I got it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And on top of the jacket, I was wearing the striped pajama jacket.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But every night, with my fingernails, I was scratching off the paint.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was-- and over and over again, it-- it was not easy, but over and over again.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
